Study regulations and academic conventions of the university are introduced. An overview is given about effective learning and means of supporting mental health. Academic reading, writing, and presenting are practiced.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give students the basic skills needed in studying in the university.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student composes a realistic study plan.  Student knows and is able to put into practice the main psychological principles of learning.  Students knows how to take care of mental health and where to seek help if needed. Student knows the basic principles of scientific communication and is able to use bibliographic data bases.  Student is able to communicate scientific material both in writing and in oral presentations.
